#Automatic Hand Sanitizer Using Raspberry Pi:-

##Hardware Requirements :- 
        Raspbeery Pi
        MG995 Servo Motor 
        HC-SR04 Ultrasonic Sensor
        Jumper Wires
        Electric Power Supply 
        Spray Bottle 
        Tapes 
        Thick copper wire 
##Connections :-
        Raspberry Pi Board Referance :-https://www.raspberrypi.org/documentation/usage/gpio/ 
        VCC( ultrasonic sensor ) - GPIO2
        Ground( ultrasonic sensor ) - GPIO6
        Trigger ( ultrasonic sensor ) - GPIO18
        Echo ( ultrasonic sensor ) - GPIO16
        Red wire ( Motor )Voltage - GPIO4
        Brown wire ( Motor )Ground - GPIO9
        Orange wire ( Motor )PWM - GPIO11
##Software Requirements :-
        GPIO Packages
        Python 
        Time 
##Setup:-
        Complete the connections as written 
        Mount the motor on Spray Bottle as shown in video example 
        Run the program 
